Magnetic Space Groups
Compiled by Harold T. Stokes and Branton J. Campbell
Brigham Young University, Provo, Utah, USA
June 2010

Table 1.  Listed in order of BNS number

BNS: Setting of N. V. Belov, N. N. Neronova and T. S. Smirnova
OG:  Setting of W. Opechowski and R. Guccione

This data is based on data from:
Daniel Litvin,"Magnetic Space Group Types," Acta Crystallographica (2001)
  A57 729-730. (http://www.bk.psu.edu/faculty/litvin/Download.html)
C. J. Bradley and A. P. Cracknell, The Mathematical Theory of Symmetry in
  Solids" (Clarendon Press, Oxford, 1972).
----------
Definition of point operator symbols (from Litvin)
Non-hexagonal groups:
1        x,y,z
4x       x,-z,y
4x-1     x,z,-y
4y       z,y,-x
4y-1     -z,y,x
4z       -y,x,z
4z-1     y,-x,z
2x       x,-y,-z
2y       -x,y,-z
2z       -x,-y,z
2xy      y,x,-z
2-xy     -y,-x,-z
2yz      -x,z,y
2-yz     -x,-z,-y
2xz      z,-y,x
2-xz     -z,-y,-x
3xyz     z,x,y
3xyz-1   y,z,x
3-xyz    -y,z,-x
3-xyz-1  -z,-x,y
3x-yz    -y,-z,x
3x-yz-1  z,-x,-y
3xy-z    y,-z,-x
3xy-z-1  -z,x,-y
-1       -x,-y,-z
-4x      -x,z,-y
-4x-1    -x,-z,y
-4y      -z,-y,x
-4y-1    z,-y,-x
-4z      y,-x,-z
-4z-1    -y,x,-z
mx       -x,y,z
my       x,-y,z
mz       x,y,-z
mxy      -y,-x,z
m-xy     y,x,z
myz      x,-z,-y
m-yz     x,z,y
mxz      -z,y,-x
m-xz     z,y,x
-3xyz    -z,-x,-y
-3xyz-1  -y,-z,-x
-3-xyz   y,-z,x
-3-xyz-1 z,x,-y
-3x-yz   y,z,-x
-3x-yz-1 -z,x,y
-3xy-z   -y,z,x
-3xy-z-1 z,-x,y
Hexagonal groups:
1        x,y,z
6z       x-y,x,z
3z       -y,x-y,z
2z       -x,-y,z
3z-1     -x+y,-x,z
6z-1     y,-x+y,z
2x       x-y,-y,-z
2xy      y,x,-z
2y       -x,-x+y,-z
21       x,x-y,-z
22       -x+y,y,-z
23       -y,-x,-z
-1       -x,-y,-z
-6z      -x+y,-x,-z
-3z      y,-x+y,-z
mz       x,y,-z
-3z-1    x-y,x,-z
-6z-1    -y,x-y,-z
mx       -x+y,y,z
mxy      -y,-x,z
my       x,x-y,z
m1       -x,-x+y,z
m2       x-y,-y,z
m3       y,x,z
----------
Magnetic Space Groups
----------
UNI: 1.1 P1.1  BNS: 1.1 P1  OG: 1.1.1 P1
Operators: (1|0,0,0)
Wyckoff positions:
1a (x,y,z;mx,my,mz)
